1
00:00:09,510 --> 00:00:12,846
NARRATOR: It is said
that in the final days of planet Earth,

2
00:00:13,347 --> 00:00:16,149
everyone had bad dreams.

3
00:00:20,854 --> 00:00:23,056
To the west of the north of that world,

4
00:00:23,423 --> 00:00:28,128
the human race did gather
in the celebration of a pagan rite

5
00:00:28,462 --> 00:00:30,697
to banish the cold and the dark.

6
00:00:34,568 --> 00:00:38,939
Each and every one of those people had
dreamt of the terrible things to come,

7
00:00:39,573 --> 00:00:43,577
but they forgot, because they must.

8
00:00:44,111 --> 00:00:49,082
They forgot their nightmares
of fire and war and insanity.

9
00:00:50,183 --> 00:00:54,288
They forgot, except for one.

10
00:00:54,855 --> 00:00:56,323
(LAUGHING MANIACALLY)

11
00:00:58,025 --> 00:00:59,226
(BAND PLAYING CAROLS)

12
00:01:08,502 --> 00:01:10,270
(CHOIR SINGING HYMN)

13
00:02:08,095 --> 00:02:10,831
WOMAN: They call it the
legend of the blue box.

14
00:02:11,131 --> 00:02:12,199
Oh...

15
00:02:12,299 --> 00:02:16,203
Well, I've never been in here before.
I'm not one for churches.

16
00:02:16,503 --> 00:02:17,537
Too cold.

17
00:02:18,805 --> 00:02:22,542
This was the site of a convent
back in the 1300s.

18
00:02:24,177 --> 00:02:29,316
It's said a demon fell from the sky.
Then a man appeared.

19
00:02:29,616 --> 00:02:31,418
A man in a blue box.

20
00:02:32,686 --> 00:02:34,855
They called him a sainted physician.

21
00:02:35,856 --> 00:02:39,192
He smote the demon and then disappeared.

22
00:02:39,860 --> 00:02:41,995
Well, that's a bit of a coincidence.

23
00:02:42,763 --> 00:02:45,365
It's said there's no such thing
as coincidence.

24
00:02:45,465 --> 00:02:46,466
(WILFRED SCOFFING)

25
00:02:46,566 --> 00:02:50,871
Who knows? Perhaps he's coming back.

26
00:02:50,971 --> 00:02:53,907
Oh, that would make my Christmas.

27
00:02:55,342 --> 00:02:56,410
Huh?

28
00:03:11,892 --> 00:03:16,530
(LAUGHING MANIACALLY)

29
00:03:21,768 --> 00:03:23,870
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

30
00:03:56,403 --> 00:04:00,307
(WHOOSHING)

31
00:04:03,310 --> 00:04:07,114
Ah! Now! Sorry! There you are.

32
00:04:08,515 --> 00:04:12,018
So, where were we?
I was summoned, wasn't I?

33
00:04:13,420 --> 00:04:16,356
An Ood in the snow, calling to me.

34
00:04:16,590 --> 00:04:18,225
Well, I didn't exactly
come straight here.

35
00:04:18,325 --> 00:04:20,794
Had a bit of fun, you know,
travelled about, did this and that.

36
00:04:20,894 --> 00:04:23,263
Got into trouble, you know me.
It was brilliant.

37
00:04:23,363 --> 00:04:27,267
I saw the phosphorous carousel
of the Great Magellan Gestalt.

38
00:04:27,701 --> 00:04:29,970
Saved a planet
from the Red Carnivorous Maw.

39
00:04:31,071 --> 00:04:34,474
Named a galaxy Allison.
Got married. That was a mistake.

40
00:04:34,574 --> 00:04:35,842
Good Queen Bess.

41
00:04:35,942 --> 00:04:38,645
And let me tell you,
her nickname is no longer...

42
00:04:39,112 --> 00:04:40,781
(CLEARING THROAT) Anyway...

43
00:04:41,915 --> 00:04:43,250
What do you want?

44
00:04:43,416 --> 00:04:45,252
You should not have delayed.

45
00:04:45,852 --> 00:04:49,089
Last time I was here,
you said my song would be ending soon.

46
00:04:49,422 --> 00:04:51,057
And I'm in no hurry for that.

47
00:04:51,625 --> 00:04:52,959
You will come with me.

48
00:04:53,059 --> 00:04:55,061
Hold on. Better lock the TARDIS.

49
00:04:56,463 --> 00:04:57,564
(BEEPING)

50
00:04:58,098 --> 00:05:02,536
See? Like a car. I locked it like a car.

51
00:05:03,937 --> 00:05:05,405
That's funny.

52
00:05:06,540 --> 00:05:08,608
No? Little bit?

53
00:05:09,776 --> 00:05:12,045
(EXCLAIMING) Blimey.
Try to make an Ood laugh...

54
00:05:14,781 --> 00:05:17,150
So, how old are you now, Ood Sigma?

55
00:05:18,418 --> 00:05:19,486
Ah!

56
00:05:20,754 --> 00:05:22,756
(DOCTOR LAUGHING)

57
00:05:22,856 --> 00:05:24,491
DOCTOR: Magnificent!

58
00:05:28,695 --> 00:05:31,231
Oh, come on! That is splendid.

59
00:05:32,699 --> 00:05:34,868
You've achieved all this in how long?

60
00:05:34,968 --> 00:05:36,102
One hundred years.

61
00:05:39,272 --> 00:05:43,476
Then we've got a problem,
'cause all this is way too fast.

62
00:05:43,944 --> 00:05:46,713
Not just the city.
I mean, your ability to call me.

63
00:05:46,813 --> 00:05:49,416
Reaching all the way back
to the 21st century.

64
00:05:51,218 --> 00:05:54,287
Something's accelerating your species
way beyond normal.

65
00:05:54,421 --> 00:05:56,890
And the mind of the Ood is troubled.

66
00:05:56,990 --> 00:05:58,158
Why? What's happened?

67
00:05:58,258 --> 00:06:02,395
Every night, Doctor.
Every night we have bad dreams.

68
00:06:03,096 --> 00:06:08,335
ELDER OOD: Returning, returning,
returning, it is slowly returning,

69
00:06:08,535 --> 00:06:12,539
to the dark and the fire and the blood,
always returning.

70
00:06:12,906 --> 00:06:15,108
Returning to this world.

71
00:06:15,308 --> 00:06:19,779
It is returning and he is returning
and they are returning,

72
00:06:19,980 --> 00:06:25,218
but too late, too late, far too late,
he has come.

73
00:06:25,986 --> 00:06:28,288
OOD: (ECHOING) He returns...

74
00:06:28,388 --> 00:06:31,558
OO0D SIGMA: Sit with the elder of the Ood
and share the dreaming.

75
00:06:31,658 --> 00:06:33,093
(ECHOING CONTINUES)

76
00:06:33,493 --> 00:06:35,896
So... Right.

77
00:06:40,066 --> 00:06:41,134
Hello.

78
00:06:43,236 --> 00:06:48,975
ELDER OOD: You will join. You will join.
You will join. You will join.

79
00:06:49,309 --> 00:06:53,513
You will join. You will join.
You will join.

80
00:06:54,447 --> 00:06:55,515
(LAUGHING)

81
00:06:55,582 --> 00:06:56,716
(GASPING)

82
00:06:56,850 --> 00:06:59,653
He comes to us, every night.

83
00:07:00,020 --> 00:07:03,757
I think all the peoples of the universe
dream of him now.

84
00:07:04,391 --> 00:07:05,592
That man is dead.

85
00:07:05,692 --> 00:07:08,662
There is yet more. Join us.

86
00:07:08,728 --> 00:07:09,763
(INHALING)

87
00:07:09,863 --> 00:07:14,668
Events are taking shape, so many
years ago and yet changing the now.

88
00:07:15,435 --> 00:07:16,436
There is a man...

89
00:07:16,536 --> 00:07:17,570
(LAUGHING MANIACALLY)

90
00:07:17,671 --> 00:07:18,705
ELDER OOD: So scared...

91
00:07:20,540 --> 00:07:23,643
Wilfred. Is he all right?
What about Donna? Is she safe?

92
00:07:23,743 --> 00:07:25,245
You should not have delayed.

93
00:07:25,345 --> 00:07:29,849
For the lines of convergence are being
drawn across the Earth even now.

94
00:07:30,050 --> 00:07:32,852
The king is in his counting house.

95
00:07:38,191 --> 00:07:39,693
I don't know who they are.

96
00:07:39,793 --> 00:07:43,296
And there is another.
The most lonely of all.

97
00:07:43,863 --> 00:07:45,732
Lost and forgotten.

98
00:07:46,366 --> 00:07:47,467
(SOBBING)

99
00:07:47,734 --> 00:07:49,436
DOCTOR: The Master's wife.

100
00:07:50,570 --> 00:07:53,807
We see so much, but understand little.

101
00:07:54,341 --> 00:07:56,409
The woman in the cage, who is she?

102
00:07:57,210 --> 00:08:01,614
She was... It wasn't her fault.
She was...

103
00:08:02,916 --> 00:08:05,051
The Master, he's a Time Lord, like me.

104
00:08:08,421 --> 00:08:09,456
I can show you.

105
00:08:12,292 --> 00:08:14,160
DOCTOR:
The Master took the name of Saxon.

106
00:08:14,260 --> 00:08:17,630
He married a human, a woman called Lucy,
and he corrupted her.

107
00:08:17,931 --> 00:08:19,032
MAN: No!

108
00:08:20,300 --> 00:08:23,770
DOCTOR: She stood at his side
while he conquered the Earth.

109
00:08:23,903 --> 00:08:26,806
I reversed everything he'd done,
so it never even happened,

110
00:08:26,906 --> 00:08:28,241
but Lucy Saxon remembered.

111
00:08:28,341 --> 00:08:29,509
(GUN FIRING)

112
00:08:33,713 --> 00:08:36,983
DOCTOR: I held him in my arms.
I burnt his body.

113
00:08:39,285 --> 00:08:40,587
The Master is dead!

114
00:08:40,687 --> 00:08:43,757
And yet you did not see.

115
00:08:45,291 --> 00:08:46,926
00D: (ECHOING) See it!

116
00:08:47,027 --> 00:08:48,194
What's that?

117
00:08:50,296 --> 00:08:52,565
(MASTER LAUGHING)

118
00:08:59,072 --> 00:09:00,573
Part of him survived.

119
00:09:02,575 --> 00:09:03,610
I have to go!

120
00:09:03,710 --> 00:09:06,179
But something more is happening, Doctor.

121
00:09:06,813 --> 00:09:09,349
The Master is part of a greater design,

122
00:09:09,716 --> 00:09:12,419
because a shadow is falling
over creation.

123
00:09:12,619 --> 00:09:15,355
Something vast is stirring in the dark.

124
00:09:18,258 --> 00:09:21,428
The Ood have gained this power
to see through time

125
00:09:21,728 --> 00:09:23,696
because time is bleeding.

126
00:09:23,797 --> 00:09:27,167
Shapes of things once lost
are moving through the veil.

127
00:09:27,333 --> 00:09:32,005
And these events from years ago
threaten to destroy this future.

128
00:09:32,539 --> 00:09:35,075
And the present and the past.

129
00:09:35,175 --> 00:09:36,209
What do you mean?

130
00:09:36,309 --> 00:09:38,711
This is what we have seen, Doctor.

131
00:09:39,412 --> 00:09:42,248
The darkness heralds only one thing,

132
00:09:43,183 --> 00:09:45,585
the end of time itself.

133
00:09:45,685 --> 00:09:46,786
(LAUGHING MANIACALLY)

134
00:09:57,230 --> 00:10:00,733
Events that have happened
are happening now.

135
00:10:23,490 --> 00:10:24,691
(BEEPING)

136
00:10:39,572 --> 00:10:43,209
Mrs Saxon, let me introduce myself.

137
00:10:44,344 --> 00:10:45,912
I'm your new governor.

138
00:10:46,779 --> 00:10:50,783
I'm afraid the previous governor
met with something of an accident,

139
00:10:51,050 --> 00:10:53,686
which took quite some time to arrange.

140
00:10:54,754 --> 00:10:57,490
Miss Trefusis, if you will prepare.

141
00:11:01,628 --> 00:11:04,230
You kept your silence well, Mrs Saxon.

142
00:11:05,231 --> 00:11:08,234
Your trial was held in secret
with no jury,

143
00:11:09,302 --> 00:11:13,506
so no one knows who Harold Saxon was,

144
00:11:14,807 --> 00:11:18,244
where he came from, why you killed him.

145
00:11:19,579 --> 00:11:21,014
Make her kneel.

146
00:11:24,851 --> 00:11:29,355
There are those of us
who never lost faith.

147
00:11:29,889 --> 00:11:34,093
And, in his wisdom, Harold Saxon
prepared for this moment.

148
00:11:34,727 --> 00:11:37,997
He knew that he might die
and he made us ready.

149
00:11:39,732 --> 00:11:41,534
Tonight, Mrs Saxon,

150
00:11:44,270 --> 00:11:45,338
he returns.

151
00:11:47,273 --> 00:11:48,374
(MASTER LAUGHING)

152
00:11:48,474 --> 00:11:49,475
(GASPING)

153
00:11:49,576 --> 00:11:51,077
(LAUGHTER CONTINUES)

154
00:11:56,015 --> 00:11:57,717
REPORTER: (ON TV)
This shocking discovery...

155
00:11:57,817 --> 00:11:59,485
(TRANSMISSION DISRUPTING)

156
00:12:02,355 --> 00:12:04,891
REPORTER ON TV:
That supports conservation...

157
00:12:06,626 --> 00:12:11,831
GOVERNOR: As it was written
in the secret books of Saxon,

158
00:12:12,732 --> 00:12:16,402
these are the potions of life.

159
00:12:16,502 --> 00:12:21,074
Listen to me. Whatever he told you,
you've got no idea what you're doing.

160
00:12:21,174 --> 00:12:24,410
Miss Trefusis, the catalyst.

161
00:12:24,978 --> 00:12:26,079
LUCY: What are you doing?

162
00:12:26,179 --> 00:12:27,647
Leave me alone! Don't!

163
00:12:28,314 --> 00:12:29,916
You were Saxon's wife.

164
00:12:30,016 --> 00:12:33,653
You bore his imprint.
That's what we needed.

165
00:12:34,254 --> 00:12:38,024
The final biometrical signature.

166
00:12:40,627 --> 00:12:43,463
(CRYING) You can't bring him back,
you can't!

167
00:12:56,175 --> 00:13:01,014
I'm begging you!
Stop this now, before it's too late!

168
00:13:01,114 --> 00:13:06,819
We give ourselves that Saxon might live!

169
00:13:10,757 --> 00:13:15,428
Can't you see? He lied to you!
His name isn't even Harold Saxon!

170
00:13:15,528 --> 00:13:19,032
GOVERNOR: And this was written also!

171
00:13:19,699 --> 00:13:25,305
For his name is the Master!

172
00:13:25,738 --> 00:13:29,676
Never. Never! Never! Never!

173
00:13:29,976 --> 00:13:36,249
Never dying. Never dying! Never dying!
Never dying! Never dying!

174
00:13:36,349 --> 00:13:37,984
(MASTER LAUGHING)

175
00:13:46,893 --> 00:13:49,262
Oh, Lucy...

176
00:13:50,296 --> 00:13:54,867
Sweet Lucy Saxon, my ever-faithful...

177
00:13:55,101 --> 00:13:58,237
Did the widow's kiss
bring me back to life?

178
00:13:58,338 --> 00:13:59,672
You're killing them!

179
00:13:59,772 --> 00:14:02,775
Oh, let them die.
They're just the first.

180
00:14:03,576 --> 00:14:06,612
The whole stupid,
stinking human disgrace

181
00:14:06,713 --> 00:14:08,448
can fall into the pit!

182
00:14:11,217 --> 00:14:12,852
Can't you hear it, Lucy?

183
00:14:13,086 --> 00:14:18,391
The noise. The drumbeat.
Louder than ever before.

184
00:14:20,893 --> 00:14:24,030
The drums, the never-ending drums.

185
00:14:25,665 --> 00:14:27,633
Oh, I have missed them.

186
00:14:27,734 --> 00:14:29,035
(MASTER CHUCKLING)

187
00:14:29,135 --> 00:14:32,705
But no one knew you better than I did.
I knew you'd come back!

188
00:14:33,206 --> 00:14:35,875
And all this time,
your disciples have prepared!

189
00:14:36,309 --> 00:14:37,710
But so have we!

190
00:14:40,179 --> 00:14:41,247
What are you doing?

191
00:14:41,347 --> 00:14:45,051
The secret books of Saxon
spoke of the potions of life,

192
00:14:46,018 --> 00:14:49,689
and I was never that bright,
but my family had contacts.

193
00:14:49,789 --> 00:14:53,726
People who were clever enough
to calculate the opposite!

194
00:14:54,026 --> 00:14:58,631
Don't you dare! I'm ordering you, Lucy!
You will obey me!

195
00:14:58,731 --> 00:15:01,834
Till death do us part, Harry!

196
00:15:01,901 --> 00:15:03,936
No!

197
00:15:10,109 --> 00:15:11,210
(PANTING)

198
00:15:32,932 --> 00:15:34,100
(DOOR OPENING)

199
00:15:35,868 --> 00:15:38,070
I think we might be in luck, darling.

200
00:15:38,171 --> 00:15:41,607
It's the footage from Broadfell Prison
the night it burnt down.

201
00:15:41,741 --> 00:15:43,209
Take a look at this.

202
00:15:47,013 --> 00:15:49,949
Someone survived? Do you think it's him?

203
00:15:51,417 --> 00:15:53,753
Oh, that would be
such a Christmas present.

204
00:15:53,820 --> 00:15:55,154
(LAUGHING)

205
00:15:55,755 --> 00:15:57,156
You just leave it to Daddy.

206
00:16:04,530 --> 00:16:07,366
Ladies and gentleman,
it seems help is at hand.

207
00:16:08,434 --> 00:16:12,238
Christmas is cancelled!
Prepare the gate!

208
00:16:29,889 --> 00:16:32,058
(WHISTLING) Just going down The Lion!

209
00:16:32,258 --> 00:16:34,827
Quick little snifter. Christmas drinks.

210
00:16:35,061 --> 00:16:36,195
All right, ta-ta!

211
00:16:40,967 --> 00:16:43,736
Parachute 1 to Parachute 2,
we are mobilised.

212
00:16:43,836 --> 00:16:47,974
I repeat, we are mobilised.
Rendezvous 1300 hours.

213
00:16:48,307 --> 00:16:49,509
Over and out.

214
00:16:54,981 --> 00:16:56,115
Come on!

215
00:16:56,215 --> 00:16:57,283
(WILFRED LAUGHING)

216
00:16:57,383 --> 00:16:59,652
Way-hey! Shake a leg! Yay-hey!

217
00:17:00,219 --> 00:17:01,254
Whoa!

218
00:17:03,756 --> 00:17:04,824
Whoop!

219
00:17:05,057 --> 00:17:06,092
(MAN WHISTLING)

220
00:17:06,192 --> 00:17:07,727
Come on! Let's get going.

221
00:17:07,827 --> 00:17:08,895
(ALL CHEERING)

222
00:17:08,995 --> 00:17:09,996
WILFRED: Off we go.

223
00:17:10,096 --> 00:17:12,899
Everybody all right?
We've got a job to do.

224
00:17:12,999 --> 00:17:14,500
(WILFRED CHEERING)

225
00:17:15,501 --> 00:17:19,472
Right, he's tall and thin.
Wears a brown suit, maybe a blue suit.

226
00:17:19,572 --> 00:17:22,775
He's got a long brown coat,
modern sort of hair.

227
00:17:22,875 --> 00:17:24,911
All sticky-uppy. All right?

228
00:17:25,011 --> 00:17:28,748
Oh, and on page two,
be on the lookout for a police box,

229
00:17:28,848 --> 00:17:30,216
exactly like the old ones.

230
00:17:30,316 --> 00:17:34,887
I got locked inside one of them.
August Bank Holiday, 1962.

231
00:17:34,987 --> 00:17:36,856
Were you misbehaving, Minnie?

232
00:17:37,256 --> 00:17:39,492
I certainly was. Way-hey!

233
00:17:39,592 --> 00:17:40,726
(ALL LAUGHING)

234
00:17:40,826 --> 00:17:42,495
Yeah. All right, all right. Now listen.

235
00:17:42,595 --> 00:17:46,098
This is important.
We have got to find it.

236
00:17:46,198 --> 00:17:48,167
Right, so phone around. Phone everybody.

237
00:17:48,267 --> 00:17:50,036
Sally, will you
get on to the Bridge Club?

238
00:17:50,136 --> 00:17:52,004
Right. Winston, you try the old boys.

239
00:17:52,104 --> 00:17:54,840
Bobby, I want you to ring, uh,
the skiffle band, right?

240
00:17:54,941 --> 00:17:56,676
Between us, we got the city covered.

241
00:17:56,776 --> 00:17:58,477
-The silver cloak.
-Yeah.

242
00:17:58,578 --> 00:18:00,379
Who is he, then, this Doctor?

243
00:18:01,314 --> 00:18:03,382
No, I can't tell you that, I swear.

244
00:18:04,850 --> 00:18:08,854
Yeah, but answer me this.
You've been having bad dreams?

245
00:18:09,555 --> 00:18:13,426
All of you? Dreams you can't remember.

246
00:18:15,194 --> 00:18:17,697
Yeah. Well, that's why we need him.

247
00:18:18,898 --> 00:18:20,700
We need the Doctor,

248
00:18:21,667 --> 00:18:22,768
more than ever.

249
00:18:26,505 --> 00:18:28,574
WOMAN: Onions with that?
MAN: Oh, yeah, go on, pile them on.

250
00:18:29,408 --> 00:18:31,277
What about you, Ginger? Onions?

251
00:18:32,311 --> 00:18:37,450
He don't say much. Give him onions.
He's down from Huddersfield.

252
00:18:37,650 --> 00:18:39,085
WOMAN: Well, you look after him.

253
00:18:39,185 --> 00:18:42,488
And don't forget, tomorrow night,
Christmas broadcast...

254
00:18:43,389 --> 00:18:44,857
-President Obama...
-Oh...

255
00:18:44,957 --> 00:18:47,093
WOMAN: He's promised
to end the recession.

256
00:18:47,193 --> 00:18:49,295
Bad times will soon be over, Ginger.

257
00:18:49,428 --> 00:18:53,199
-Well, season's greetings to you.
-WOMAN: And you. Happy Christmas!

258
00:18:56,869 --> 00:18:58,771
Now, what can we get you, sir?

259
00:19:02,074 --> 00:19:03,175
Everything.

260
00:19:06,846 --> 00:19:09,782
I am so hungry.

261
00:19:10,516 --> 00:19:12,018
(MASTER LAUGHING)

262
00:19:13,019 --> 00:19:16,055
They're saying that the President's
got this grand plan.

263
00:19:16,555 --> 00:19:20,159
He's gonna save the world
with some big financial scheme.

264
00:19:21,127 --> 00:19:23,629
Whatever it is,
bet it won't reach you and me.

265
00:19:25,097 --> 00:19:27,366
Uh-oh, somebody's lively on his feet.

266
00:19:30,336 --> 00:19:31,437
Starving.

267
00:19:42,848 --> 00:19:45,051
Now, you see,
that's what you don't want to do.

268
00:19:45,151 --> 00:19:47,787
Eat it all at once. Tempting, I know,

269
00:19:48,254 --> 00:19:50,790
but if you make it last,
it can last all day.

270
00:19:50,890 --> 00:19:52,191
MASTER: I want more.

271
00:19:52,291 --> 00:19:54,560
Cheese and chips and meat and gravy

272
00:19:54,660 --> 00:19:56,529
and cream and beer and pork and beef

273
00:19:56,629 --> 00:19:59,398
and fat and great big chunks
of hot, wet, red...

274
00:19:59,498 --> 00:20:00,933
Good for you, mate.

275
00:20:01,100 --> 00:20:02,868
Well, we'd better be going.

276
00:20:03,569 --> 00:20:06,906
(STUTTERING) You look like that bloke.
Harold Saxon.

277
00:20:07,206 --> 00:20:08,507
The one that went mad.

278
00:20:08,574 --> 00:20:09,709
(LAUGHING)

279
00:20:10,710 --> 00:20:11,977
(LAUGHING)

280
00:20:12,344 --> 00:20:13,579
Now, isn't that funny?

281
00:20:15,147 --> 00:20:17,349
Isn't that just the best thing of all?

282
00:20:18,851 --> 00:20:24,290
The master of disguise, stuck
looking like the old Prime Minister.

283
00:20:24,557 --> 00:20:28,427
(LAUGHING) I can't hide anywhere.
He can see me.

284
00:20:29,528 --> 00:20:33,099
He can smell me.
I can't let him smell me.

285
00:20:33,199 --> 00:20:35,634
Doctor, Doctor, Doctor, Doctor,
got to stop the smell!

286
00:20:35,735 --> 00:20:38,337
The stink! The filthy, filthy stink!

287
00:20:39,505 --> 00:20:41,874
Ginger, come with me! Right now!

288
00:20:42,074 --> 00:20:45,111
Because it's funny! Don't you see?

289
00:20:46,779 --> 00:20:50,516
Look at me! I'm splitting my sides!

290
00:20:50,583 --> 00:20:52,218
I am hilarious!

291
00:20:52,651 --> 00:20:56,021
I am the funniest thing
in the whole wide world!

292
00:20:56,789 --> 00:20:57,957
(ROARING)

293
00:20:58,057 --> 00:20:59,592
(MASTER LAUGHING)

294
00:21:08,267 --> 00:21:09,435
Save us!

295
00:21:09,969 --> 00:21:12,905
God help us! There's this man!

296
00:21:18,144 --> 00:21:21,113
Dinnertime!

297
00:21:24,216 --> 00:21:25,251
MAN: No!

298
00:21:25,351 --> 00:21:27,119
(BOTH SCREAMING)

299
00:21:33,425 --> 00:21:34,927
(SHIP'S HORN BLOWING)

300
00:21:43,435 --> 00:21:45,504
(INHALING)

301
00:21:54,180 --> 00:21:55,614
(INHALING)

302
00:22:13,666 --> 00:22:15,034
(BARREL CLANGING)

303
00:23:03,382 --> 00:23:04,416
(SCREAMING)

304
00:23:11,857 --> 00:23:13,392
(MASTER LAUGHING)

305
00:23:33,812 --> 00:23:35,314
(DOCTOR PANTING)

306
00:23:36,415 --> 00:23:38,517
(LAUGHING)

307
00:23:38,584 --> 00:23:39,618
(ROARING)

308
00:23:39,952 --> 00:23:44,023
Please, let me help!
You're burning up your own life force.

309
00:23:44,223 --> 00:23:45,257
(GROWLING)

310
00:23:45,357 --> 00:23:47,593
(MASTER LAUGHING)

311
00:23:48,427 --> 00:23:50,429
Oh, my gosh, Doctor,
you're a sight for sore eyes.

312
00:23:50,529 --> 00:23:51,997
-Out of my way!
-Oh? |

313
00:23:52,231 --> 00:23:53,399
(LAUGHING)

314
00:23:53,499 --> 00:23:55,534
MAN 1: Did we do it? Yeah! Is that him?

315
00:23:55,634 --> 00:23:57,536
MAN 2: Tall and thin. Big brown coat.

316
00:23:57,636 --> 00:23:58,938
MINNIE: The silver cloak.

317
00:23:59,038 --> 00:24:02,408
It worked, 'cause Will phoned Nettie,
who phoned June.

318
00:24:02,508 --> 00:24:06,578
And her sister lives opposite Broadfell
and she saw the police box.

319
00:24:06,679 --> 00:24:09,748
And her neighbour saw this man
heading east.

320
00:24:09,848 --> 00:24:12,718
Wilfred, have you told them who I am?
You promised me...

321
00:24:12,818 --> 00:24:14,520
No, I just said you were a doctor,
that's all.

322
00:24:14,620 --> 00:24:18,290
Hmm. And might I say, sir,
it is an honour to see you again.

323
00:24:19,658 --> 00:24:22,661
Oh! But you never said he was a looker.

324
00:24:22,995 --> 00:24:26,699
-He's gorgeous! Take a photo.
-Not bad, eh?

325
00:24:26,799 --> 00:24:28,667
-ALL: No...
-V nice.

326
00:24:28,767 --> 00:24:31,170
I'm Minnie. Minnie the Menace.

327
00:24:31,303 --> 00:24:34,406
It's a long time since I had a photo
with a handsome man.

328
00:24:34,506 --> 00:24:36,408
Could you just get off him?
Leave him alone!

329
00:24:36,508 --> 00:24:41,013
Hush, you old misery. Come on, Doctor.
Give us a smile.

330
00:24:41,513 --> 00:24:43,248
-That's it!
-MAN: Hold on.

331
00:24:43,782 --> 00:24:46,719
-Did it flash?
-No, there's a blue light. Try again.

332
00:24:46,819 --> 00:24:48,387
I'm all fingers and thumbs.

333
00:24:48,487 --> 00:24:50,289
I'm really kind of busy, you know.

334
00:24:50,389 --> 00:24:52,391
Oh, it won't take a tick. Keep smiling.

335
00:24:54,259 --> 00:24:56,261
Is that your hand, Minnie?

336
00:24:56,862 --> 00:24:58,030
Good boy.

337
00:25:02,868 --> 00:25:06,472
WILFRED: All right, let's...
Come on, then! Here we are. Hurry up.

338
00:25:07,439 --> 00:25:10,476
WILFRED: Goodbye. Go on.

339
00:25:12,511 --> 00:25:13,946
Come on, over here.

340
00:25:14,279 --> 00:25:15,681
DOCTOR: Well, what's so special
about this place?

341
00:25:15,781 --> 00:25:17,316
We passed 15 cafes on the way.

342
00:25:17,416 --> 00:25:20,019
(LAUGHING) Yeah. Afternoon.

343
00:25:22,087 --> 00:25:23,856
WILFRED: But we had some good times,
didn't we, though?

344
00:25:23,956 --> 00:25:27,459
I mean, all those Atmos things
and planets in the sky

345
00:25:27,559 --> 00:25:29,161
and me with that paint gun.

346
00:25:29,261 --> 00:25:30,396
(IMITATES PAINT GUN FIRING)

347
00:25:32,998 --> 00:25:34,333
(WILFRED EXHALING)

348
00:25:35,768 --> 00:25:40,305
I keep seeing things, Doctor,
I... This face at night.

349
00:25:40,939 --> 00:25:42,107
Who are you?

350
00:25:43,575 --> 00:25:44,943
I'm Wilfred Mott.

351
00:25:45,277 --> 00:25:47,713
No. People have waited
hundreds of years to find me,

352
00:25:47,813 --> 00:25:49,648
and then you manage it
in a couple of hours.

353
00:25:49,748 --> 00:25:51,250
Well, I'm just lucky, I suppose.

354
00:25:51,350 --> 00:25:53,218
No, we keep on meeting, Wilf.

355
00:25:53,318 --> 00:25:55,988
Over and over again,
like something's still connecting us.

356
00:25:56,088 --> 00:25:58,323
Yeah, but what's so important about me?

357
00:25:58,424 --> 00:25:59,825
Exactly. Why you?

358
00:26:09,435 --> 00:26:10,769
I'm going to die.

359
00:26:11,770 --> 00:26:14,173
-Well, so am I, one day.
-Don't you dare.

360
00:26:14,339 --> 00:26:15,574
All right, I'll try not to.

361
00:26:15,674 --> 00:26:16,975
(CHUCKLING)

362
00:26:18,911 --> 00:26:20,345
But I was told.

363
00:26:21,947 --> 00:26:23,715
He will knock four times.

364
00:26:24,850 --> 00:26:26,018
(INHALING)

365
00:26:26,118 --> 00:26:27,519
That was a prophecy.

366
00:26:28,153 --> 00:26:29,721
Knock four times and then...

367
00:26:29,822 --> 00:26:33,025
Yeah, but I thought...
When I saw you before, you said that

368
00:26:33,358 --> 00:26:37,129
your people could change, like,
your whole body.

369
00:26:37,463 --> 00:26:38,797
I can still die.

370
00:26:40,299 --> 00:26:43,068
If I'm killed before regeneration,
then I'm dead.

371
00:26:45,270 --> 00:26:46,738
Even then...

372
00:26:48,173 --> 00:26:50,809
Even if I change, it feels like dying.

373
00:26:55,380 --> 00:26:56,915
Everything I am dies.

374
00:26:58,117 --> 00:27:00,385
Some new man goes sauntering away.

375
00:27:05,357 --> 00:27:06,558
And I'm dead.

376
00:27:09,895 --> 00:27:12,631
-Hmm...
-What? Oh...

377
00:27:13,132 --> 00:27:15,234
I'm sorry, but I had to...

378
00:27:15,334 --> 00:27:17,136
-Look, can't you make her better?
-Stop it.

379
00:27:17,236 --> 00:27:19,538
No, but you're so clever.
Can't you bring her memory back?

380
00:27:19,638 --> 00:27:22,074
Look... Just go to her now, go on.
Just run across the street.

381
00:27:22,174 --> 00:27:23,575
Go up and say, "Hello".

382
00:27:23,675 --> 00:27:27,312
If she ever remembers me,
her mind will burn and she will die.

383
00:27:28,113 --> 00:27:29,248
(CAR DOOR CLOSING)

384
00:27:29,348 --> 00:27:32,050
Don't you touch this car!

385
00:27:32,151 --> 00:27:33,619
(DOCTOR AND WILFRED LAUGHING)

386
00:27:34,186 --> 00:27:35,521
She's not changed.

387
00:27:35,587 --> 00:27:36,822
WILFRED: No...

388
00:27:38,190 --> 00:27:39,458
Oh, there he is.

389
00:27:40,492 --> 00:27:43,495
Shawn Temple. They're engaged.

390
00:27:44,329 --> 00:27:46,131
Getting married in the spring.

391
00:27:47,099 --> 00:27:49,168
-Another wedding?
-Yeah.

392
00:27:50,302 --> 00:27:52,471
Hold on, she's not gonna be called
Noble Temple?

393
00:27:52,571 --> 00:27:55,874
-That sounds like a tourist spot.
-No, it's Temple Noble.

394
00:27:55,941 --> 00:27:57,109
Right.

395
00:27:58,677 --> 00:28:01,180
Is she happy? Is he nice?

396
00:28:02,281 --> 00:28:05,017
Yeah, he's sweet enough.
He's a bit of a dreamer.

397
00:28:05,951 --> 00:28:08,420
Mind you, he's on minimum wage.
She's earning tuppence,

398
00:28:08,520 --> 00:28:11,056
so all they can afford
is a tiny, little flat.

399
00:28:12,424 --> 00:28:15,194
And then sometimes
I see this look on her face.

400
00:28:15,627 --> 00:28:19,798
Like she's so sad,
but she can't remember why.

401
00:28:22,434 --> 00:28:23,635
She's got him.

402
00:28:25,103 --> 00:28:26,438
She's making do.

403
00:28:27,306 --> 00:28:28,507
Aren't we all?

404
00:28:31,143 --> 00:28:32,611
Yeah, how about you?

405
00:28:33,412 --> 00:28:35,380
-Who have you got now?
-No one.

406
00:28:37,449 --> 00:28:38,984
I'm travelling alone.

407
00:28:42,654 --> 00:28:44,890
I thought it would be better alone.

408
00:28:47,626 --> 00:28:49,895
But I did some things that went wrong.

409
00:28:51,263 --> 00:28:52,431
I need...

410
00:28:52,864 --> 00:28:53,899
Oh, my word...

411
00:28:53,999 --> 00:28:55,067
(DOCTOR GASPING)

412
00:28:55,133 --> 00:28:56,168
(EXHALES)

413
00:28:57,069 --> 00:28:58,136
Uh...

414
00:28:59,238 --> 00:29:00,339
Merry Christmas.

415
00:29:00,439 --> 00:29:01,540
Yeah, and you.

416
00:29:01,640 --> 00:29:03,075
(BOTH LAUGHING)

417
00:29:03,408 --> 00:29:04,543
Look at us.

418
00:29:05,177 --> 00:29:07,045
WILFRED: Well, don't you...
Don't you see?

419
00:29:07,145 --> 00:29:09,381
You know, you need her, Doctor!
I mean...

420
00:29:09,581 --> 00:29:12,651
Look, wouldn't she make you laugh again?
Good, old Donna.

421
00:29:19,424 --> 00:29:21,293
Eh? Hmm?

422
00:29:38,810 --> 00:29:42,848
NARRATOR: And so it came to pass that
the players took their final places,

423
00:29:43,515 --> 00:29:46,018
making ready the events
that were to come.

424
00:29:51,590 --> 00:29:57,462
The madman sat in his empire
of dust and ashes,

425
00:29:58,430 --> 00:30:01,233
little knowing of the glory
he would achieve,

426
00:30:04,269 --> 00:30:07,472
while his saviour
looked upon the wilderness

427
00:30:08,140 --> 00:30:12,210
in the hope of changing
his inevitable fate.

428
00:30:15,614 --> 00:30:21,787
Far away, the idiots and fools
dreamt of a shining new future.

429
00:30:22,554 --> 00:30:25,424
A future now doomed to never happen.

430
00:30:27,259 --> 00:30:30,028
As Earth rolled onwards into night,

431
00:30:30,929 --> 00:30:35,167
the people of that world
did sleep and shiver,

432
00:30:36,101 --> 00:30:41,540
somehow knowing
the dawn would bring only one thing.

433
00:30:45,177 --> 00:30:47,012
The final day.

434
00:31:18,310 --> 00:31:19,544
(ELECTRICITY SURGING)

435
00:32:01,853 --> 00:32:02,954
(GROANING)

436
00:32:11,663 --> 00:32:12,697
(GROANING)

437
00:32:23,809 --> 00:32:25,610
I had estates.

438
00:32:27,813 --> 00:32:30,715
Do you remember
my father's land back home?

439
00:32:32,217 --> 00:32:38,390
Pastures of red grass stretching far
across the slopes of Mount Perdition.

440
00:32:40,492 --> 00:32:41,626
(SIGHING)

441
00:32:42,794 --> 00:32:48,066
We used to run across those fields
all day, calling up at the sky.

442
00:32:53,338 --> 00:32:54,806
Look at us now.

443
00:32:56,675 --> 00:32:58,109
All that eloquence.

444
00:32:59,311 --> 00:33:01,780
But how many people have you killed?

445
00:33:04,216 --> 00:33:05,951
I am so hungry.

446
00:33:06,051 --> 00:33:08,587
Your resurrection went wrong.

447
00:33:08,687 --> 00:33:12,824
That energy... Your body's ripped open.

448
00:33:14,226 --> 00:33:15,594
Now you're killing yourself.

449
00:33:15,694 --> 00:33:18,330
And that's human Christmas out there.

450
00:33:19,164 --> 00:33:21,066
They eat so much!

451
00:33:21,466 --> 00:33:25,604
All that roasting meat,
cakes and red wine.

452
00:33:25,704 --> 00:33:28,673
Hot, fat, blood food.

453
00:33:28,773 --> 00:33:34,813
Pots, plates of meat and flesh
and grease and juice.

454
00:33:34,913 --> 00:33:37,682
And baking, burnt, sticky, hot skin.

455
00:33:37,782 --> 00:33:39,050
Hot! It's so hot!

456
00:33:39,150 --> 00:33:40,652
-Stop it!
-Slice!

457
00:33:40,752 --> 00:33:41,920
-Slice!
-Stop it!

458
00:33:42,020 --> 00:33:44,089
It's mine! It's mine!
It's mine! It's mine!

459
00:33:44,189 --> 00:33:46,992
-Eat it! Eat it! Eat it! Eat it!
-Stop it!

460
00:33:52,697 --> 00:33:54,766
What if I ask you for help?

461
00:33:55,433 --> 00:33:56,535
(EXCLAIMING)

462
00:33:57,802 --> 00:33:58,937
(SNICKERING)

463
00:33:59,538 --> 00:34:01,540
There are more at work tonight
than you and me.

464
00:34:02,173 --> 00:34:03,408
Oh, yeah?

465
00:34:03,508 --> 00:34:06,211
I've been told something is returning.

466
00:34:06,945 --> 00:34:08,580
And here I am.

467
00:34:09,648 --> 00:34:10,949
No, something more.

468
00:34:11,016 --> 00:34:12,117
But it hurts.

469
00:34:12,217 --> 00:34:14,653
-I was told the end of time...
-It hurts...

470
00:34:14,753 --> 00:34:16,321
Doctor, the noise.

471
00:34:17,055 --> 00:34:19,457
The noise in my head, Doctor.

472
00:34:20,258 --> 00:34:23,161
One, two, three, four. One, two,
three, four. One, two, three, four.

473
00:34:23,261 --> 00:34:24,963
Stronger than ever before.

474
00:34:27,432 --> 00:34:29,000
Can't you hear it?

475
00:34:29,901 --> 00:34:31,703
Listen, listen, listen, listen.

476
00:34:31,803 --> 00:34:33,572
(RHYTHMIC TAPPING)

477
00:34:34,773 --> 00:34:37,175
Every minute, every second,

478
00:34:38,510 --> 00:34:40,745
every beat of my hearts,

479
00:34:42,280 --> 00:34:43,748
there it is,

480
00:34:44,816 --> 00:34:46,351
calling to me.

481
00:34:47,953 --> 00:34:49,387
Please listen.

482
00:34:49,454 --> 00:34:50,855
I can't hear it.

483
00:34:53,692 --> 00:34:54,859
Listen!

484
00:34:58,029 --> 00:34:59,731
(BANGING TAPPING)

485
00:34:59,831 --> 00:35:00,899
(GASPING)

486
00:35:02,534 --> 00:35:03,602
What?

487
00:35:04,302 --> 00:35:05,403
I._..

488
00:35:06,404 --> 00:35:08,139
-What?
-I heard it.

489
00:35:10,175 --> 00:35:11,710
But that's no noise.

490
00:35:11,810 --> 00:35:14,179
There never has been,
it's just your insanity.

491
00:35:15,580 --> 00:35:19,551
What is it? What's inside your head?

492
00:35:19,651 --> 00:35:22,187
(LAUGHING DELIRIOUSLY) It's real.

493
00:35:24,589 --> 00:35:25,824
It's real!

494
00:35:26,891 --> 00:35:28,493
It's real!

495
00:35:36,935 --> 00:35:38,570
(MASTER LAUGHING)

496
00:35:46,778 --> 00:35:50,448
All these years you thought I was mad!

497
00:35:53,752 --> 00:35:55,654
King of the wasteland.

498
00:35:56,888 --> 00:36:01,126
But something is calling me, Doctor.
What is it? What is it?

499
00:36:01,226 --> 00:36:02,427
What is it?

500
00:36:13,405 --> 00:36:14,939
(HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING)

501
00:36:17,709 --> 00:36:18,810
(YELLING)

502
00:36:24,949 --> 00:36:26,051
No!

503
00:36:38,463 --> 00:36:39,964
Let him go!

504
00:36:58,349 --> 00:37:00,518
(MERRY XMAS, EVERYBODY BY SLADE
PLAYING ON RADIO)

505
00:37:06,091 --> 00:37:07,325
Now then, steady on.

506
00:37:07,425 --> 00:37:09,928
It's never too early for margaritas,
that's what I say.

507
00:37:10,028 --> 00:37:12,630
I forgot to get lemons
so I used oranges instead.

508
00:37:12,731 --> 00:37:14,232
It's all fruit, same difference.

509
00:37:14,332 --> 00:37:19,304
Oh, now that's lovely. Look at that!
Absolutely beautiful.

510
00:37:20,371 --> 00:37:22,807
Oh, "Love from Donna."
Did you keep the receipt?

511
00:37:22,907 --> 00:37:24,275
Yes, I did.

512
00:37:24,375 --> 00:37:27,512
Come on, Gramps. You've been
a right misery ever since you got up.

513
00:37:27,612 --> 00:37:29,280
Do you like it then, the book?

514
00:37:29,380 --> 00:37:32,250
Joshua Naismith?
I mean, what did you get me this for?

515
00:37:33,151 --> 00:37:34,819
I don't know.

516
00:37:34,919 --> 00:37:39,090
I just saw it in the shop
and thought of you.

517
00:37:40,558 --> 00:37:42,894
It just felt like
the sort of thing you should have.

518
00:37:43,528 --> 00:37:46,164
SYLVIA: (LAUGHING)
Oh, now, look at that.

519
00:37:46,264 --> 00:37:49,400
That's from Charlie Morton.
Isn't that rude?

520
00:37:49,501 --> 00:37:50,969
(BOTH LAUGHING)

521
00:37:58,309 --> 00:37:59,577
If you would, Mr Danes.

522
00:38:04,282 --> 00:38:05,750
I'm starving.

523
00:38:05,984 --> 00:38:07,852
You have my daughter to thank for this.

524
00:38:08,720 --> 00:38:10,221
It's all her idea.

525
00:38:10,989 --> 00:38:14,058
She heard rumours of Harold Saxon,
his disciples, his return.

526
00:38:15,360 --> 00:38:18,463
It's the sort of thing
she finds rather thrilling.

527
00:38:18,563 --> 00:38:24,068
And I was right. He's back.
The very man we need and he's here.

528
00:38:24,936 --> 00:38:28,740
Oh, this is gonna be wonderful.

529
00:38:33,945 --> 00:38:35,680
Aye-aye! Here are the presents.

530
00:38:35,780 --> 00:38:36,848
(ALL EXCLAIMING)

531
00:38:36,948 --> 00:38:38,516
I'm sorry I couldn't afford much.
But not for long.

532
00:38:38,616 --> 00:38:41,519
Not if President Obama ends
the recession tonight. Come here!

533
00:38:41,619 --> 00:38:43,621
WILFRED: Whoa, whoa, whoa,
keep it quiet, you lot.

534
00:38:43,721 --> 00:38:45,123
It's the Queen's Speech. Now, come on.

535
00:38:45,223 --> 00:38:46,558
Sit down, show respect. Come on.

536
00:38:46,658 --> 00:38:47,992
-Merry Christmas, Mr Mott.
-Thank you.

537
00:38:48,092 --> 00:38:50,862
Will you behave! Honestly.

538
00:38:50,962 --> 00:38:53,998
All right now. She's on, she's on.
It's our sovereign.

539
00:38:59,604 --> 00:39:00,705
Eh?

540
00:39:02,707 --> 00:39:04,742
Events are moving, Wilfred.

541
00:39:04,843 --> 00:39:07,445
-Eh?
-Faster than we thought.

542
00:39:07,545 --> 00:39:08,880
Can you see that?

543
00:39:08,980 --> 00:39:11,850
Frankly, I'd tell Her Majesty
it's time for trouser suits.

544
00:39:11,950 --> 00:39:13,885
No, no, no, no. That's not...

545
00:39:14,385 --> 00:39:16,521
Only you can see.

546
00:39:16,621 --> 00:39:19,591
Only you stand
at the heart of coincidence.

547
00:39:19,691 --> 00:39:20,959
Why? What have I done?

548
00:39:21,059 --> 00:39:23,127
You're an old soldier, sir.

549
00:39:23,828 --> 00:39:25,964
Only you were too late.

550
00:39:26,064 --> 00:39:28,566
The war was won and passed you by.

551
00:39:28,666 --> 00:39:30,068
I did my duty.

552
00:39:30,802 --> 00:39:33,004
You never killed a man.

553
00:39:33,104 --> 00:39:36,541
No, I didn't. No, I did not, no,

554
00:39:36,641 --> 00:39:38,643
but don't say that like it's shameful.

555
00:39:39,811 --> 00:39:43,381
A time will come
when you must take arms.

556
00:39:44,048 --> 00:39:45,483
Who are you?

557
00:39:47,051 --> 00:39:48,786
Tell the Doctor nothing of this.

558
00:39:49,888 --> 00:39:52,090
His life could still be saved,

559
00:39:53,024 --> 00:39:55,660
so long as you tell him nothing.

560
00:40:01,799 --> 00:40:02,901
Did...

561
00:40:05,837 --> 00:40:07,105
(SIGHING)

562
00:40:09,540 --> 00:40:11,609
(WOMEN LAUGHING)

563
00:40:37,468 --> 00:40:38,803
(CLATTERING ON GLASS)

564
00:40:57,789 --> 00:40:58,923
I lost him.

565
00:40:59,023 --> 00:41:01,826
I was unconscious. He's still on Earth.
I can smell him, but he's too far away.

566
00:41:01,926 --> 00:41:04,162
Listen, you can't park there.
What if Donna sees it?

567
00:41:04,262 --> 00:41:05,964
You're the only one, Wilf.

568
00:41:06,064 --> 00:41:08,099
The only connection I can think of.
You're involved.

569
00:41:08,199 --> 00:41:09,834
If I could just work out how.

570
00:41:09,934 --> 00:41:11,736
Tell me, have you seen anything?

571
00:41:11,836 --> 00:41:14,072
I don't know.
Anything strange, anything odd?

572
00:41:14,172 --> 00:41:15,907
-Well, there was...
-What?

573
00:41:16,007 --> 00:41:17,575
-What is it? Tell me!
-Well, it...

574
00:41:17,942 --> 00:41:18,977
Nah, it's nothing.

575
00:41:19,077 --> 00:41:20,878
Think, think, think!
Maybe something out of the blue.

576
00:41:20,979 --> 00:41:22,380
Something connected to your life.
Something!

577
00:41:22,480 --> 00:41:24,916
Well, Donna was a bit strange.

578
00:41:25,016 --> 00:41:28,419
She had a funny, little moment
this morning all because of that book.

579
00:41:28,486 --> 00:41:29,587
What book?

580
00:41:30,488 --> 00:41:32,056
Here you are,
his name's Joshua Naismith.

581
00:41:32,156 --> 00:41:33,558
That's the man.

582
00:41:33,658 --> 00:41:34,659
I was shown him by the Ood.

583
00:41:34,759 --> 00:41:35,793
-The what?
-By the Ood.

584
00:41:35,893 --> 00:41:37,128
-What's the Ood?
-They're just the Ood.

585
00:41:37,228 --> 00:41:39,564
But it's all part of the convergence
maybe...

586
00:41:40,498 --> 00:41:42,800
Maybe touching Donna's subconscious.

587
00:41:45,036 --> 00:41:48,606
Oh, she's still fighting for it,
even now. The Doctor Donna.

588
00:41:48,706 --> 00:41:50,375
Dad, what are you up to?

589
00:41:51,376 --> 00:41:54,946
You! But... Get out of here!

590
00:41:55,046 --> 00:41:56,948
-Merry Christmas.
-Merry Christmas.

591
00:41:57,048 --> 00:41:58,983
But she can't see you!
What if she remembers?

592
00:41:59,083 --> 00:42:01,119
DONNA: Mum, where are those tweezers?

593
00:42:01,219 --> 00:42:02,220
-Go!
-I'm going.

594
00:42:02,320 --> 00:42:03,388
Yeah, me, too.

595
00:42:03,488 --> 00:42:04,756
Oh, no, you don't.

596
00:42:06,324 --> 00:42:09,227
Mum? Gramps?

597
00:42:10,261 --> 00:42:13,197
-Dad, I'm warning you!
-Bye, see you later.

598
00:42:13,998 --> 00:42:15,600
I'm a bit old for hide-and-seek.

599
00:42:15,700 --> 00:42:17,135
Stay right where you are!

600
00:42:17,735 --> 00:42:19,537
-You can't come with me.
-You're not leaving me with her.

601
00:42:19,637 --> 00:42:20,805
-Dad!
-Fair enough.

602
00:42:20,938 --> 00:42:22,540
-DONNA: Mum?
-Just you listen to me.

603
00:42:22,640 --> 00:42:25,176
I forbid it! Get out of there!

604
00:42:25,276 --> 00:42:28,579
Doctor, bring my father back right now!

605
00:42:29,680 --> 00:42:31,082
Come back here!

606
00:42:31,682 --> 00:42:34,786
Come back here, I said. Come back!

607
00:42:35,520 --> 00:42:37,955
Are you shouting at thin air?

608
00:42:39,057 --> 00:42:40,158
Yes.

609
00:42:41,459 --> 00:42:43,027
Possibly. Yes.

610
00:42:45,363 --> 00:42:46,597
Naismith!

611
00:42:47,765 --> 00:42:49,667
If I can track him down...

612
00:42:51,202 --> 00:42:53,704
Ah! Right. Yes.

613
00:42:54,906 --> 00:42:57,108
Bigger on the inside. Do you like it?

614
00:42:57,208 --> 00:42:59,043
I thought it'd be cleaner.

615
00:42:59,143 --> 00:43:00,378
Cleaner?

616
00:43:01,045 --> 00:43:03,081
I can take you back home right now.

617
00:43:03,181 --> 00:43:06,951
Listen, Doctor. If this is
a time machine, that man you're chasing,

618
00:43:07,051 --> 00:43:09,720
why can't you just pop back
to yesterday and catch him?

619
00:43:09,821 --> 00:43:11,622
I can't go back inside my own timeline.

620
00:43:11,722 --> 00:43:14,392
I have to stay relative to the Master
within the causal matrix.

621
00:43:14,492 --> 00:43:16,527
-Understand?
-Not a word.

622
00:43:16,627 --> 00:43:18,296
-Welcome aboard.
-Thank you.

623
00:43:31,175 --> 00:43:32,543
You can demonstrate.

624
00:43:43,888 --> 00:43:45,523
Oh, that's not from Earth.

625
00:43:46,657 --> 00:43:50,528
And neither are you.
A perfect combination, don't you think?

626
00:43:51,062 --> 00:43:53,798
(CLEARING THROAT) Uh, excuse me, sir.
If I could check the basement?

627
00:43:53,898 --> 00:43:56,367
We're getting fluctuation
on the power cord.

628
00:43:56,467 --> 00:43:57,935
-Of course.
-Miss Addams.

629
00:43:58,035 --> 00:44:00,371
If you could bring
the calibration statistics?

630
00:44:16,354 --> 00:44:18,623
Who the hell is he?
What if he finds out?

631
00:44:18,723 --> 00:44:22,026
An expert, they said.
Well, what sort of expert?

632
00:44:22,126 --> 00:44:24,395
-Who is he?
-I don't know!

633
00:44:25,530 --> 00:44:28,666
According to the records,
Harold Saxon was Prime Minister

634
00:44:28,766 --> 00:44:31,102
of this stupid country.

635
00:44:31,202 --> 00:44:33,437
I am choking in this thing!

636
00:44:33,538 --> 00:44:34,639
I'm sorry.

637
00:44:36,674 --> 00:44:37,742
(SIGHING)

638
00:44:37,842 --> 00:44:41,078
Oh, by the saints, that's better.

639
00:44:41,179 --> 00:44:44,015
Oh, these people are so flat.

640
00:44:46,784 --> 00:44:47,885
(GROANING)

641
00:44:48,319 --> 00:44:49,954
Well, what do we do?

642
00:44:50,054 --> 00:44:52,456
We were so close.
We almost had it working!

643
00:44:52,557 --> 00:44:55,226
What if this visitor
is some sort of genius?

644
00:44:56,327 --> 00:44:59,764
Well, think about it.
We are hijacking this project.

645
00:44:59,864 --> 00:45:01,632
Maybe we can use him, too.

646
00:45:01,732 --> 00:45:05,069
Harold Saxon or whatever he is

647
00:45:05,169 --> 00:45:08,005
might be exactly what we need.

648
00:45:09,240 --> 00:45:11,842
The gate was found inside a spaceship

649
00:45:11,943 --> 00:45:13,911
buried at the foot of Mount Snowdon.

650
00:45:14,011 --> 00:45:16,480
It was moved to an institute
known as Torchwood.

651
00:45:16,581 --> 00:45:18,216
But when Torchwood fell,

652
00:45:19,417 --> 00:45:21,652
let's just say I acquired it.

653
00:45:24,622 --> 00:45:26,023
I like you.

654
00:45:26,457 --> 00:45:27,491
Thank you.

655
00:45:28,226 --> 00:45:30,161
You'd taste great.

656
00:45:32,530 --> 00:45:33,898
Mr Danes.

657
00:45:35,266 --> 00:45:36,901
The visitor will be given food.

658
00:45:38,736 --> 00:45:39,837
Ah.

659
00:46:10,167 --> 00:46:14,238
Anyway, the device came equipped
with its own power supply.

660
00:46:15,806 --> 00:46:17,541
A nuclear bolt.

661
00:46:17,642 --> 00:46:21,812
One technician remains in charge
of the feedback 24 hours a day.

662
00:46:21,912 --> 00:46:24,181
And the power feeds through to the gate.

663
00:46:24,782 --> 00:46:27,985
It encourages some sort of
cellular regeneration.

664
00:46:28,085 --> 00:46:30,321
Miss Hollands was our test subject.

665
00:46:30,421 --> 00:46:33,424
She carried some burns as result of
an accident when she was a child,

666
00:46:33,524 --> 00:46:35,993
down her left side. If you could...

667
00:46:38,562 --> 00:46:39,897
The gate mended her.

668
00:46:41,499 --> 00:46:42,533
Thank you.

669
00:46:42,933 --> 00:46:44,502
But what do you want it for?

670
00:46:44,602 --> 00:46:48,639
We calculate that, if this device can be
fully repaired by your good self,

671
00:46:48,739 --> 00:46:51,475
it can restore the body forever.

672
00:46:51,575 --> 00:46:54,645
Hence its given title,
The Immortality Gate.

673
00:46:54,745 --> 00:46:58,516
Because that's what I want.
Not for me, but for my daughter.

674
00:46:59,784 --> 00:47:03,321
I want her never to die. My gift to her.

675
00:47:04,422 --> 00:47:07,224
She will be immortal.

676
00:47:08,392 --> 00:47:12,530
Abigail. It means, "Bringer of joy".

677
00:47:20,604 --> 00:47:21,672
(INHALING)

678
00:47:26,277 --> 00:47:27,645
Better get to work.

679
00:47:32,416 --> 00:47:34,452
We've moved! We really moved!

680
00:47:34,552 --> 00:47:36,587
-You should stay here.
-Not bloody likely.

681
00:47:36,687 --> 00:47:38,356
And don't swear. Hold on.

682
00:47:41,125 --> 00:47:42,360
Just a second out of synch.

683
00:47:42,460 --> 00:47:43,761
Don't want the Master
finding the TARDIS.

684
00:47:43,861 --> 00:47:44,895
That's the last thing we need.

685
00:47:55,973 --> 00:47:59,577
That book said he's a billionaire.
He's got his own private army.

686
00:48:00,578 --> 00:48:01,712
Stay here.

687
00:48:03,280 --> 00:48:04,815
(ELECTRONIC BUZZING)

688
00:48:15,793 --> 00:48:17,294
Miss Addams, we're getting
some encouraging results

689
00:48:17,395 --> 00:48:19,196
from the ratio foldback.
Can you confirm?

690
00:48:19,797 --> 00:48:22,933
The man's a miracle. All the systems
are slotting back into place.

691
00:48:23,033 --> 00:48:25,436
Shatter treads have harmonised,
the fibre links have densified.

692
00:48:25,536 --> 00:48:27,204
Multiple overshots have triplicated...

693
00:48:27,304 --> 00:48:28,906
-Nice gate!
-Hello!

694
00:48:29,006 --> 00:48:30,841
Look, sorry, don't try calling security

695
00:48:30,941 --> 00:48:32,777
or I'll tell them
you're wearing a shimmer.

696
00:48:32,877 --> 00:48:35,679
'Cause I reckon anyone wearing a shimmer
doesn't want the shimmer to be noticed

697
00:48:35,780 --> 00:48:37,415
or they wouldn't need a shimmer
in the first place.

698
00:48:37,515 --> 00:48:40,384
I'm sorry, what's a shimmer?

699
00:48:40,451 --> 00:48:42,286
Shimmer.

700
00:48:42,353 --> 00:48:43,621
(SIGHING)

701
00:48:43,721 --> 00:48:46,257
Oh, my Lord. She's a cactus.

702
00:48:46,857 --> 00:48:49,093
Miss Addams? Miss Addams?

703
00:48:50,761 --> 00:48:52,463
If you'll would just excuse me.

704
00:48:55,833 --> 00:48:58,869
Now, please don't imagine
I'm a slave driver.

705
00:48:58,969 --> 00:49:01,071
You can resume work
on Boxing Day, Mr Saxon.

706
00:49:01,672 --> 00:49:02,873
My name

707
00:49:04,775 --> 00:49:06,143
is the Master.

708
00:49:19,223 --> 00:49:23,527
Oh, excellent! Excellent!

709
00:49:25,262 --> 00:49:27,498
-Mr Danes.
-The visitor will be restrained.

710
00:49:28,332 --> 00:49:30,434
What? But I repaired it.

711
00:49:30,534 --> 00:49:34,572
I'm not an idiot!
Don't let him anywhere near that thing.

712
00:49:36,874 --> 00:49:38,042
(LAUGHING)

713
00:49:41,979 --> 00:49:43,914
He's got it working, but what is it?

714
00:49:44,515 --> 00:49:47,051
What's working? What are you doing here?

715
00:49:47,818 --> 00:49:49,620
Shimmer!

716
00:49:51,755 --> 00:49:55,192
Now, tell me quickly, what's going on,
the Master, Harold Saxon?

717
00:49:55,292 --> 00:49:58,095
Skeletor, whatever you're calling him,
what's he doing up there?

718
00:49:59,897 --> 00:50:01,765
Your reputation precedes you, sir.

719
00:50:02,533 --> 00:50:04,735
I have no doubt you've laid traps.

720
00:50:04,835 --> 00:50:10,307
Perhaps explosives,
a means of escape and murder.

721
00:50:10,407 --> 00:50:12,877
But everything you've done to the gate
will be checked and double-checked

722
00:50:12,977 --> 00:50:15,179
before anyone stands inside.

723
00:50:18,415 --> 00:50:21,785
But I checked the readings.
He's done good work. It's operational.

724
00:50:21,886 --> 00:50:23,420
Who are you, though?
"Cause I met someone like you.

725
00:50:23,521 --> 00:50:25,523
He was brilliant,
but he was little and red.

726
00:50:25,623 --> 00:50:27,391
No, that's a Zocci.

727
00:50:27,491 --> 00:50:29,360
We're not Zocci, we're Vinvocci.

728
00:50:29,460 --> 00:50:32,396
-Completely different.
-ADDAMS: And the gate is Hipocci.

729
00:50:32,830 --> 00:50:34,098
We're a salvage team.

730
00:50:34,198 --> 00:50:36,634
We picked up a signal
when the humans re-activated it.

731
00:50:36,734 --> 00:50:39,336
And as soon as it's working,
we can transport it to the ship.

732
00:50:39,570 --> 00:50:41,438
But what does it do?

733
00:50:41,539 --> 00:50:43,474
Well, it mends. It's as simple as that.

734
00:50:43,574 --> 00:50:46,010
It's a medical device
to repair the body.

735
00:50:46,110 --> 00:50:47,645
It makes people better.

736
00:50:48,712 --> 00:50:51,448
No, there's got to be more.

737
00:50:52,383 --> 00:50:55,753
Every single warning says the Master
is gonna do something colossal.

738
00:50:55,853 --> 00:50:58,155
So that thing is like a sick-bed, yeah?

739
00:50:58,255 --> 00:50:59,990
-More or less.
-WILFRED: Well, pardon me for asking,

740
00:51:00,090 --> 00:51:01,425
but why is it so big?

741
00:51:01,525 --> 00:51:04,261
Oh, good question. Why is it so big?

742
00:51:04,361 --> 00:51:07,498
(SCOFFING) It doesn't just mend
one person at a time.

743
00:51:08,499 --> 00:51:10,301
(CHUCKLING) That would be ridiculous.

744
00:51:10,401 --> 00:51:12,937
It mends whole planets.

745
00:51:15,172 --> 00:51:16,273
It does what?

746
00:51:17,041 --> 00:51:20,110
It transmits the medical template
across the entire population.

747
00:51:30,554 --> 00:51:32,089
Come on, it's time for the broadcast.

748
00:51:33,891 --> 00:51:37,161
President's grand initiative.
You might want to see this, sir.

749
00:51:37,261 --> 00:51:39,797
Proof that the human race
can mend its own problems.

750
00:51:40,230 --> 00:51:45,035
And now, anticipation is rising
as we go live to Washington.

751
00:51:45,469 --> 00:51:48,939
Here, on Christmas Day,
the President has promised

752
00:51:49,039 --> 00:51:53,277
an instant and radical solution
to the worldwide depression.

753
00:51:53,444 --> 00:51:58,382
Barack Obama will lead us all
into a new age of prosperity.

754
00:51:58,749 --> 00:52:02,219
WOMAN: Ladies and gentlemen,
the President of the United States.

755
00:52:04,054 --> 00:52:07,658
I'd like to speak briefly
about the state of our economy.

756
00:52:07,891 --> 00:52:09,760
Turn the gate off right now!

757
00:52:09,860 --> 00:52:10,961
Man arms!

758
00:52:11,061 --> 00:52:14,231
No, no, no, no. Whatever you do,
just don't let him near that device!

759
00:52:14,331 --> 00:52:17,301
Oh, like that was ever gonna happen.

760
00:52:21,538 --> 00:52:23,007
(SCREAMING)

761
00:52:28,879 --> 00:52:32,650
Homeless, was I? Destitute and dying?

762
00:52:32,750 --> 00:52:34,418
Well, look at me now!

763
00:52:35,152 --> 00:52:37,921
Deactivate it!
All of you, turn the whole thing off!

764
00:52:38,689 --> 00:52:39,890
(MASTER LAUGHING)

765
00:52:39,990 --> 00:52:42,893
He's inside my head.

766
00:52:44,328 --> 00:52:45,429
(MASTER LAUGHING)

767
00:52:46,230 --> 00:52:47,531
Get out of there!

768
00:52:49,533 --> 00:52:54,238
Doctor! Doctor, there's this face...

769
00:52:54,638 --> 00:52:57,641
-What is it? What can you see?
-Well, it's him. I can see him.

770
00:52:58,308 --> 00:52:59,343
I can see his face.

771
00:52:59,443 --> 00:53:00,978
Something's wrong.

772
00:53:01,078 --> 00:53:03,313
It seems to be affecting the President.

773
00:53:04,882 --> 00:53:06,450
(MASTER LAUGHING)

774
00:53:09,720 --> 00:53:12,890
-I can't turn it off!
-That's because I locked it, idiot.

775
00:53:12,956 --> 00:53:14,258
Wilfred!

776
00:53:15,559 --> 00:53:17,094
Get inside, get him out!

777
00:53:19,329 --> 00:53:20,397
Get out!

778
00:53:22,966 --> 00:53:24,902
Just need to filter the levels.

779
00:53:25,002 --> 00:53:27,571
Oh! I can see again! He's gone!

780
00:53:27,671 --> 00:53:29,373
Radiation shielding.
Now press the button, let me out!

781
00:53:29,440 --> 00:53:30,474
You what?

782
00:53:30,574 --> 00:53:32,910
I can't get out until you
press the button. That button there!

783
00:53:35,412 --> 00:53:36,980
Fifty seconds and counting.

784
00:53:37,047 --> 00:53:38,182
To what?

785
00:53:38,282 --> 00:53:40,250
Oh, you're gonna love this.

786
00:53:42,052 --> 00:53:43,721
He was hiding the codes.

787
00:53:43,821 --> 00:53:46,457
He's extrapolated the gate pattern
a million times over!

788
00:53:46,557 --> 00:53:48,258
It's not affecting us.

789
00:53:48,358 --> 00:53:50,694
He set the template to human!

790
00:53:52,129 --> 00:53:54,431
(MOBILE PHONE RINGING)

791
00:53:54,531 --> 00:53:55,799
Hello... Oh.

792
00:54:01,171 --> 00:54:02,639
-Donna'!
-Where are you?

793
00:54:02,973 --> 00:54:04,908
It's Mum and Shawn.
Something's wrong with them.

794
00:54:05,008 --> 00:54:06,243
There's his face.

795
00:54:06,810 --> 00:54:07,878
(MASTER LAUGHING)

796
00:54:08,779 --> 00:54:11,915
Wait a minute. I mean, what about you?
Can't you see anything?

797
00:54:12,015 --> 00:54:14,251
I can see them. That's bad enough.

798
00:54:14,351 --> 00:54:16,820
Not now, Winston!

799
00:54:16,920 --> 00:54:19,890
Wilfred! Those dreams...

800
00:54:19,990 --> 00:54:22,493
I can remember that face!

801
00:54:23,093 --> 00:54:25,796
There's a face in my head!

802
00:54:26,230 --> 00:54:27,331
Wilfred?

803
00:54:28,999 --> 00:54:30,167
It's everyone!

804
00:54:30,434 --> 00:54:32,970
What is it, hypnotism? Mind control!

805
00:54:33,070 --> 00:54:35,172
You're grafting your thoughts
inside them, is that it?

806
00:54:35,272 --> 00:54:37,174
Oh, that's way too easy.

807
00:54:37,274 --> 00:54:40,377
No, no, no.
They're not gonna think like me.

808
00:54:40,477 --> 00:54:42,179
They're gonna become me.

809
00:54:44,248 --> 00:54:47,518
And...begin!

810
00:54:54,391 --> 00:54:57,361
(MASTER LAUGHING)

811
00:55:19,416 --> 00:55:21,418
-He can't have!
-What is it?

812
00:55:28,992 --> 00:55:30,194
(GASPING)

813
00:55:33,330 --> 00:55:37,034
They've changed. Granddad.

814
00:55:37,134 --> 00:55:41,338
It's like...like the sort of thing
that happened before!

815
00:55:42,072 --> 00:55:45,409
My head! Oh, my head! My head!

816
00:55:47,511 --> 00:55:50,681
Doctor! She's starting to remember.

817
00:55:54,151 --> 00:55:57,988
What is it? What have you done,
you monster?

818
00:55:58,088 --> 00:55:59,890
Oh, I'm sorry. Are you talking to me?

819
00:56:01,091 --> 00:56:02,159
Or to me?

820
00:56:03,560 --> 00:56:04,628
Or to me?

821
00:56:05,629 --> 00:56:06,763
Or to me?

822
00:56:08,932 --> 00:56:10,434
ALL: Or to us?

823
00:56:10,767 --> 00:56:14,071
Breaking news. I'm everyone.

824
00:56:14,171 --> 00:56:16,840
And everyone in the world is me!

825
00:56:17,174 --> 00:56:20,377
I'm President.
President of the United States!

826
00:56:20,444 --> 00:56:21,879
Look at me!

827
00:56:22,846 --> 00:56:24,114
-Whoo!
-Come on!

828
00:56:25,015 --> 00:56:28,051
Ooh. Financial solution...deleted.

829
00:56:28,118 --> 00:56:29,319
(LAUGHING)

830
00:56:33,657 --> 00:56:36,293
The human race was
always your favourite, Doctor.

831
00:56:37,194 --> 00:56:40,664
But now, there is no human race.

832
00:56:40,764 --> 00:56:44,635
There is only the Master race!

833
00:56:45,569 --> 00:56:47,337
(LAUGHING)

834
00:57:40,290 --> 00:57:44,227
NARRATOR: And so it came to pass
on Christmas Day

835
00:57:45,028 --> 00:57:48,298
that the human race did cease to exist.

836
00:57:49,333 --> 00:57:50,834
But even then,

837
00:57:50,934 --> 00:57:54,972
the Master had no concept
of his greater role in events,

838
00:57:55,072 --> 00:57:59,076
for this was far more
than humanity's end.

839
00:58:01,111 --> 00:58:05,148
This day was the day
upon which the whole of creation

840
00:58:05,248 --> 00:58:08,185
would change forever.

841
00:58:08,285 --> 00:58:12,656
This was the day
the Time Lords returned.

842
00:58:13,690 --> 00:58:14,992
For Gallifrey.

843
00:58:15,092 --> 00:58:16,560
ALL: For Gallifrey.

844
00:58:16,626 --> 00:58:18,028
For victory!

845
00:58:18,128 --> 00:58:19,296
ALL: For victory!

846
00:58:19,396 --> 00:58:23,233
For the end of time itself!

847
00:58:23,333 --> 00:58:27,070
ALL: For the end of time itself!

848
00:59:05,075 --> 00:59:07,210
WOMAN: This is
the Doctor's final battle.

849
00:59:09,046 --> 00:59:13,683
He must stand at arms
or lose himself and all this world.

850
00:59:13,784 --> 00:59:15,318
(LAUGHING)

851
00:59:15,419 --> 00:59:16,787
NARRATOR: A rhythm of four.

852
00:59:19,022 --> 00:59:21,958
The heartbeat of a Time Lord.

853
00:59:23,660 --> 00:59:25,095
WILFRED: The Master is gonna kill you.

854
00:59:27,731 --> 00:59:28,865
Kill him first.

855
00:59:28,932 --> 00:59:29,966
(GUNSHOT)

856
00:59:30,067 --> 00:59:31,435
At last.

857
00:59:31,535 --> 00:59:33,937
Sometimes, I think
a Time Lord lives too long.

